Arahathan	Letherii mage and commander of the mage cadre in the Cold Clay Battalion, counted among the three most powerful mages of the North alongside Nekal Bara and Enedictal. He dressed in black furs and coordinated with fellow sorcerers on major magical operations in service of the Letherii Empire under direction of the Ceda.<br>
Badar	An unblooded Tiste Edur warrior of the Hiroth village, assigned to Sergeant Canarth's squad in Trull Sengar's military company. He participates in the campaign against the Letherii Empire, serving as messenger and taking part in early engagements including operations at Narrow Chute bridge.<br>
Biri	A Letherii merchant in Letheras, owner of a warehouse at the end of Cul Street near Quillas Canal. He holds dredging rights to the canal and employs Chalas as a watchman. Perpetually overstocked, he claims street space for overflow goods. He nurses a bitter grudge against Tehol Beddict over past financial losses.<br>
Brys Beddict	Youngest of the three Beddict brothers, serving as Finadd of the Royal Guard and King's Champion of Lether — widely regarded as the finest swordsman in the kingdom. Calm brown eyes and martial bearing mark his appearance. He is drawn to the fighting arts for their relative simplicity and self-discipline, seeking order through mastery of the blade. Privately conflicted about family ties, particularly regarding his brother Hull's disgrace, he is nonetheless defined by unwavering duty and honour.<br>
Bubyrd	Sorcerer and board member of the Rat Catchers' Guild in Letheras. He possesses significant magical abilities and a deep preoccupation with rodents that manifests in his work.<br>
Bugg	Unpaid manservant to Tehol Beddict in Letheras — an elderly, grizzled, mostly bald man with watery eyes and a body covered in old scars. A former embalmer who still offers his services to those in need, he is also the frontman of Bugg's Construction and Tehol's closest associate in both legitimate and questionable ventures. His skills span knitting, engineering, and dry wit, and he is notoriously loud in his sleep. Known in criminal circles as the Waiting Man.<br>
Buruk the Pale	Head of a Letherii merchant house from Trate with long experience trading among the Arapay and Hiroth Tiste Edur tribes. He travels to Edur lands on a merchant mission accompanied by his Acquitor Seren Pedac. A man tormented by conscience, he turns increasingly to drink and indulgence, growing ever more morose as events unfold around him.<br>
Canarth	A Tiste Edur sergeant of the Hiroth tribe, commanding one of the squads in Trull Sengar's military company. Outspoken and willing to challenge his commander's decisions publicly, he nonetheless shows loyalty to his soldiers — dragging wounded men from the fray when needed.<br>
Chalas	Watchman employed at Biri's merchant yard in Letheras. He has red-shot eyes and carries a battered leather-wrapped clout at his belt. Conscientious in guarding his employer's goods, he is also compassionate toward vulnerable individuals and maintains cordial relations with Tehol Beddict despite Biri's animosity toward him.<br>
Choram Irard	A young unblooded Tiste Edur warrior and close companion of Rhulad Sengar, counted among his brothers of blood. He shows strong loyalty to Rhulad and contempt toward those he views as outsiders or slaves.<br>
Corlo	Full name Corlo Orothos. High Mage of the Second Blade, Fourth Company of the Crimson Guard, a long-standing member since the First Induction though not an Avowed. Round-faced and bearded, he wears gloves and a crimson surcoat, sometimes carrying a diadem in his left hand to amplify his Mockra magic — a warren specialising in the manipulation of minds and perception. Originally from Avore in the Kingdom of Unta. He acts as a mentor in warren magic and demonstrates refined, clever combat technique, though stress sometimes causes his hands to shake.<br>
Delisp	Matron of the Temple Brothel in Letheras. Short and lithe with a tiny waist and small feet, she has a sweet heart-shaped face with notably large eyes and a soft voice, typically dressed in close-fitting rust-coloured silks with a broad belt and upturned slippers. Beneath her gentle appearance she is watchful and protective of her establishment, willing to use a knife to defend it, and fair-minded toward those who help her.<br>
Enedictal	A Letherii mage and commander of the mage cadre within the Snakebelt Battalion, stationed at the city of Awl. Counted alongside Nekal Bara and Arahathan as one of the three most powerful mages of the North in Lether. He served the Empire under orders from King Ezgara Diskanar, participating in major coordinated magical operations against Tiste Edur settlements.<br>
Ezgara Diskanar	King of the Kingdom of Lether, a Letherii human in his sixth decade whose features remain surprisingly youthful. Lean with an asymmetrical face — the result of a childhood horse injury that left one cheekbone and eye flatter and larger than the other — he prefers modest clothing over royal regalia. Nervous in energy yet obstinate by nature, he refused magical healing of his injury out of sheer stubbornness. He leads one royal faction alongside First Eunuch Nifadas and the Ceda Kuru Qan, opposed to the Queen's rival court.<br>
Fear Sengar	Eldest son of Tomad and Uruth Sengar, and Weapons Master of the Hiroth tribe and later of all unified Tiste Edur tribes. Tall and broad-shouldered with dark eyes matching his father's, Fear is a determined, strongly-willed leader — preeminent among Hiroth warriors and pivotal in the War of Unification. He carries more trophies than any of his brothers and is betrothed to Mayen. His loyalty to family and duty is absolute, though it sometimes brings him into tension with those who question his decisions.<br>
Feather Witch	An eighteen-year-old Letherii woman born into slavery within a Tiste Edur village, serving as handmaiden to Mayen of House Sengar. Beautiful with thick long yellow hair, grey-blue eyes, and a small, child-like build hardened by years of labour, she possesses a rare supernatural gift for casting the Tiles — the Letherii analogue to reading the Deck of Dragons. Her talent for divination emerged before the age of four through prophetic dreams guided by ancestral spirits. Intelligent, perceptive, and fiercely independent, she nurses her resentments thoughtfully and is unafraid to challenge authority when circumstances demand it.<br>
Gerun Eberict	A Finadd in the Letherii Palace Guard, recognisable across the city by his flat, scarred face with thin eyebrows and the gap in his front teeth — the result of a knife wound that left him with a faint whistling breath. He gained unusual immunity from normal legal constraints through an incident involving the king's security, a privilege he reportedly exploited to pursue personal vendettas. He maintains a list of those who have displeased him and is driven by ruthlessness and paranoia.<br>
Glisten	A board member of the Rat Catchers' Guild in Letheras, one of six alongside Bubyrd, Onyx, Ormly, Ruby, and Scint. She is blonde and unusually petite — when seated at the board table, only her shoulders and head rise above its level. Her voice is described as plaintive.<br>
Green Pig	A Letherii sorcerer of old, now deceased, whose magical ability was said to have nearly rivalled that of Ceda Kuru Qan — making him one of the most powerful mages in Letherii history. He was known for overconfidence, a trait those who knew him considered defining. He is referenced in accounts of the Tolls Repository of Letheras, described as an impregnable target that no one ever successfully robbed.<br>
Halfpeck	A soldier in Iron Bars' Second Blade, Fourth Company of the Crimson Guard, wearing a crimson surcoat over his armour. Pragmatic and attentive to detail — he reworked inferior Letherii saddle stirrups to meet Guard standards — he combines dry humour with military professionalism, offering candid commentary on difficult situations and maintaining resilience and camaraderie under harsh conditions.<br>
Hannan Mosag	Warlock King of the six Tiste Edur tribes, having unified them through the War of Unification. Of average height and build with unusually pale skin and wide-set eyes that convey perpetual surprise, he dresses as a warrior but bears no martial trophies. His defining feature is a rich, deep, commanding voice. Since childhood, visions have guided his decisions. He wields Kurald Emurlahn magic and maintains power by holding the firstborn sons of subjugated chieftains as hostages and apprentices — his K'risnan network. He lives ascetically, keeping no wife, slaves, or elaborate possessions, and is protected at all times by a silent shadow wraith.<br>
Harlest	Full name Harlest Eberict; brother to Finadd Gerun Eberict, serving as a household guard on the Eberict estate. He has a pale complexion and a dry, deadpan sense of humour.<br>
Hejun	A half-blooded Faraed woman employed by Tehol Beddict in Letheras, working alongside Rissarh and Shand. She has honey-coloured skin, dark upturned eyes, and dark hair framing a heart-shaped face. Brawny and intimidating, she is willing to engage in confrontations when necessary and shows fierce determination in pursuing her goals.<br>
Hulad	A Letherii slave serving in the household of Theradas and Midik Buhn among the Hiroth Tiste Edur. He has a lined face and considers Udinaas a close friend, speaking the Meckros traders' tongue with him in private. Loyal and observant, he warns Udinaas of potential dangers after witnessing supernatural events, and assists with significant practical tasks in the household.<br>
Hulbat	A merchant citizen of Letheras with a crude and teasing sense of humour. He was among the crowd at The Drownings watching Ublala Pung, where he engaged in ribald banter at the expense of his companion Inchers.<br>
Hull Beddict	Eldest of the three Beddict brothers, formerly a Finadd, Preda, and ultimately a Sentinel for the Kingdom of Lether — tasked with studying the northern tribes. Tall and imposing with pale braided hair and grey eyes weathered by years in the wilderness, he bears three bar tattoos beneath his left shoulder given by the Tarthenal and typically wears white northern wolf furs. Possessed of a strong moral compass and said to be immune to corruption, he developed deep bonds with the northern tribal peoples and grew profoundly disillusioned with Letherii imperial policy.<br>
Huldo	Proprietor of an establishment on Red Lane in Letheras that serves as both a restaurant and entertainment venue, including a private sanctum known as The Pits for those with money and discreet business. He also operates as a minor money lender. Financially irresponsible, he spends considerable time losing money at The Drownings gaming hall. Urul serves as his chief server.<br>
Inchers	A merchant citizen of Letheras, present among the crowd at The Drownings watching Ublala Pung. He is portrayed as somewhat lecherous and defensively self-conscious, observed by his companion Hulbat taking an unusual interest in the Tarthenal's physique.<br>
Iron Bars	An Avowed leader of the Second Blade, Fourth Company of the Crimson Guard, serving under Cal-Brinn. A burly, scarred veteran with cool blue eyes, a clean-shaven face, and shoulder-length hair the hue of polished iron, he wears a blood-red surcoat. Exceptionally loyal and duty-driven, he fights with weapons and bare hands alike, possessing abnormal strength. Known among soldiers for being first to wake and preparing meals for others, he shows genuine care for those under his command. His defining quality is sheer will over combat skill.<br>
Janall	Full name Janall Diskanar; Queen of the Kingdom of Lether and wife of King Ezgara Diskanar, mother to Prince Quillas. Described as beautiful, ambitious, and greedy, she leads her own political faction against the King's, commanding the Queen's Battalion and maintaining her own keep at Dissent. When equipped for battle she wears elaborate armour with a silver and gold filigreed helm, a beaded tabard, and a pearl-studded Letherii sword. Court rumours suggest romantic attachment to her First Consort, Turudal Brizad.<br>
Kettle	A young girl, apparently nine or ten years old, with pale skin, long matted hair, and dark eyes. She lives near the Azath Tower in Letheras and is connected to it in ways that are not immediately apparent. Despite her unsettling appearance she displays a childlike nature, emotional vulnerability, and a longing for family connection.<br>
Kholb Harat	A young unblooded Tiste Edur warrior and close companion of Rhulad Sengar, counted among his brothers of blood. Ruthless and prone to violence, he demonstrates strong contempt toward outsiders and those he perceives as enemies, and is associated with Choram Irard and Matra Brith.<br>
Kuru Qan	Ceda — King's Sorcerer — to King Ezgara Diskanar of the Kingdom of Lether. A small and ancient man who wears wire-bound glass lenses of his own design that make his eyes appear enormous to onlookers. His chambers in the Old Palace are filled with furniture, scrolls, and arcane implements. Scholarly and intellectually curious, he works within a tradition of sorcery predating the current empire and is skilled in divination through the Tiles of the Holds. He holds particular fondness for Brys Beddict.<br>
Laerdas	A mage in the retinue of Prince Quillas Diskanar, one of four sorcerers accompanying the prince and First Eunuch Nifadas on diplomatic negotiations with the Tiste Edur. He is affiliated with the Letherii court and serves in a supporting magical capacity during the delegation.<br>
Mape	A female Nacht — a Jaghut-bred creature related to the bhoka'rala. Roughly a metre tall, muscle-bound, black-skinned, hairless, and black-tailed, with a perfectly round head, an apish face, small black eyes, pointed ears, and fangs. She stands out among her kind for a constant smile and an unsettling degree of intelligence in her eyes. Companion to Withal the weaponsmith, she serves alongside the other Nachts Pule and Rind, and is notably the most active and initiative-taking of the three.<br>
Mayen	A young Tiste Edur noblewoman betrothed to Fear Sengar of House Sengar. Willow-thin with darker skin than most Edur, striking green eyes, and long umber hair adorned with onyx beads, she dresses in elaborate garments befitting her station. Highly conscious of her beauty and inclined to use it for influence, she is imperious toward those beneath her station yet capable of moral judgment. She is served by the handmaiden Feather Witch.<br>
Matra Brith	A young unblooded Tiste Edur warrior and close companion of Rhulad Sengar, counted among his brothers of blood alongside Choram Irard and Kholb Harat. Loyal to Rhulad, he shows contempt toward Letherii slaves and outsiders.<br>
Midik Buhn	Second son of the Buhn bloodline and brother to Theradas, a Tiste Edur warrior of the Hiroth tribe. A childhood companion of Rhulad Sengar, he is a skilled swordsman whom Rhulad considered nearly his equal with a blade. He participated in the expedition into the Ice Fields alongside the Sengar brothers, working as a team with Theradas in dangerous encounters.<br>
Moroch Nevath	A Finadd serving as bodyguard to Prince Quillas Diskanar, and the prince's candidate for King's Champion. Possessed of incorruptible loyalty, a bold manner, and a daunting presence, he is an exceptional swordsman capable of drawing his blade in a single heartbeat — surpassed only by Brys Beddict, an assessment Moroch himself disputes. He accompanied the prince on diplomatic missions to the Tiste Edur.<br>
Nekal Bara	Resident sorceress of the city of Trate in the Letherii Empire, counted among the three most powerful mages of the North alongside Arahathan and Enedictal. Her magical energies manifest as blue fire, and she dresses in blue silks. Her power was described as approaching that of the legendary Ceda Kuru Qan. She commands mage cadres and demonstrates courage and tactical intelligence in the defence of Trate.<br>
Nifadas	First Eunuch of the Letherii royal court and trusted advisor to King Ezgara Diskanar. A large, heavy-set man with small, placid eyes set in folds of pink flesh, a small mouth, plump hands, and slow, measured movements. Widely respected for his intellect and unwavering loyalty to the king, his position as a eunuch granting him an outsider's objectivity in court affairs. He is protected by the Rulith, an elite corps of unusually fit eunuchs who serve as his personal bodyguards.<br>
Nisall	First Concubine to King Ezgara Diskanar, a position she has held for three years. Though her title carries no official power, she compensates through force of personality and sophisticated understanding of palace politics. Aligned with the King's faction against the Queen's, she participates actively in strategic planning and is perceptive, confident, and capable of holding her own in high-stakes court negotiations. She maintains close relationships with three handmaidens, the most senior of whom is Tissin.<br>
Onyx	A board member of the Rat Catchers' Guild in Letheras, one of six alongside Bubyrd, Glisten, Ormly, Ruby, and Scint. A roundish woman with tiny dark eyes and a mass of upright black hair that crawls with rats. She dislikes indecisiveness and employs intimidation when negotiating.<br>
Ormly	Champion rat catcher of the Rat Catchers' Guild and one of its board members in Letheras. A gnarled little man with yellow-tinted silver hair, a pale and deeply lined face, a broad forehead, and narrow-set eyes. He claims every rat in Letheras knows his name. Practical and somewhat indecisive, he shows nervousness about risky schemes and serves as a liaison between guild operations and external parties.<br>
Padderunt	Elderly assistant at the Stinking House in Letheras, working under the mortician Selush. A wrinkled old man with an eternally sour expression, he is irritable and cantankerous when his sleep is disturbed. Knowledgeable about rustleaf tea, which he actively promotes, and practical about financial matters — he charges clients for meals without hesitation.<br>
Prist	A large and muscular gardener employed at Gerun Eberict's estate in Letheras. Easily distracted and susceptible to fatigue, he is portrayed as oblivious to suspicious activity occurring within the household.<br>
Pule	A young male Nacht — a Jaghut-bred creature related to the bhoka'rala. Roughly a metre tall, muscle-bound, black-skinned, hairless, and black-tailed, with a perfectly round head, yellow-shot eyes, pointed ears, and fangs. He engages in repetitive, elaborate nest-building from natural materials and communicates through physical displays. Playful and mischievous, he travels as a companion to Withal the weaponsmith alongside the other Nachts Mape and Rind.<br>
Quillas Diskanar	Prince and heir to the throne of the Kingdom of Lether, son of King Ezgara Diskanar and Queen Janall. Commands his own military unit, the Quillas Brigade, and is politically aligned with his mother and Chancellor Triban Gnol. Known for expensive tastes in clothing. Observed by Hull Beddict to have limited political acumen, his awareness of his own ignorance making him suspicious of those who speak above his understanding. He is protected by a personal guard commanded by Finadd Moroch Nevath.<br>
Rethal	A Tiste Edur warrior of the Hiroth tribe, commanding a squad under Trull Sengar during the campaign against the Letherii Empire. He demonstrates tactical competence and the ability to anticipate his commander's plans during military operations, including engagements to secure strategic positions.<br>
Rhulad Sengar	Youngest of the four Sengar brothers, son of Tomad and Uruth. A handsome young Tiste Edur warrior with clear grey eyes who begins the story as an unblooded youth eager to prove himself. Brash and unsubtle, he craves validation and recognition within his warrior culture. His father Tomad was frequently and publicly dismissive of his immaturity. He participates in quests and expeditions on behalf of the Tiste Edur.<br>
Rind	An elderly male Nacht — a Jaghut-bred creature related to the bhoka'rala. Roughly a metre tall, muscle-bound, black-skinned, hairless, and black-tailed, with a perfectly round head, yellow-tinged eyes, pointed ears, and fangs. He watches his companions with detached amusement and laughs hysterically at their antics. Playful and mischievous, he travels as a companion to Withal the weaponsmith alongside Mape and Pule.<br>
Rissarh	A half-blooded Tarthenal woman employed by Tehol Beddict in Letheras, working alongside Hejun and Shand. She has sun-bleached fiery-red wavy hair reaching her broad shoulders, a classically strong face, and blue eyes of serene indifference. Brawny and intimidating, she is driven by a desire to see justice for her subjugated tribal people and approaches her work with determination and a suspicious, combative nature.<br>
Rud Elalle	A child raised among the Bentract Imass in the Refugium. He has remarkable yellow eyes and sun-bleached brown hair worn in the Bentract Imass style. Protective by nature and multilingual, he serves as a leader and protector of the Bentract community.<br>
Ruby	A board member of the Rat Catchers' Guild in Letheras, one of six alongside Bubyrd, Glisten, Onyx, Ormly, and Scint.<br>
Rucket	Chief Investigator of the Rat Catchers' Guild in Letheras. Tall and lithe with reddish hair cut short and tawny eyes that appear more feline than human. She initially wears pale South Nerek leathers, later a cape and polished boots with a rapier, and employs magical disguises when conducting business outside the guild's headquarters. Clever and courageous, she describes herself as unusually open and candid, and is willing to behave erratically to discourage unwanted visitors. She maintains loyalty to allies while exercising professional composure.<br>
Scabandari Bloodeye	Also known as Scara Bandaris and Father Shadow, a Tiste Edur commander and Soletaken Eleint capable of taking the form of a vast iron-hued dragon with ice-blue eyes. In his Tiste Edur form he has skin the shade of hammered iron, long grey hair, a gaunt aquiline face with hard close-set eyes, and white diagonal scars across his dusky skin. He carries a two-handed sword, long-knives, and a shadow-etched dagger, and wears a scaled cape made from the skin of a K'Chain Che'Malle. A military commander of stern demeanour, he served as captain and cohort commander in Urusander's Legion in ancient times and is the father of Sheltatha Lore.<br>
Scint	A board member of the Rat Catchers' Guild in Letheras, one of six alongside Bubyrd, Glisten, Onyx, Ormly, and Ruby. He takes absurd proposals with literal seriousness and is known for impulsive behaviour.<br>
Selush	A skilled mortician and beautician who operates the Stinking House in Letheras, assisted by Padderunt. Tall and amply proportioned, she has a distinctive arrangement of twenty-seven short black braids projecting in different directions, each wrapped around an antler tine, violet eyes, and full red lips. She possesses formidable talent as a disguiser of flaws and specialises in the careful preparation of corpses using fragrant oils, cinnamon, and myrrh. Resourceful and enterprising, she adapts her craft to new circumstances with business acumen.<br>
Seren Pedac	A Letherii Acquitor — one of only seven permitted by treaty to operate in Tiste Edur lands — and a naturally gifted practitioner of Mockra magic. She typically wears an umber fur cloak, fur-lined gloves, and sometimes leather armour with a helm. Skilled with a sword and experienced on horseback. Thoughtful and introspective, she spent most of her life among men and felt excluded from female companionship. She is drawn to people in suffering and is cynical about political justifications for violence, viewing claims of destiny as excuses used to evade accountability for wrongdoing.<br>
Shand	An employee of Tehol Beddict in Letheras, working alongside Hejun and Rissarh as part of his inner circle and assisting with his financial schemes and ventures in the city.<br>
Shurq Elalle	A renowned thief of Letheras with a legendary reputation in the criminal underworld. She dresses in black silks beneath a short black calf-hide jacket, tanned leggings, high boots, and leather gloves. Resourceful and professional, she is commanding in her dealings and adapts to circumstances with cunning and skill.<br>
Strong Rall	A cut-throat operating in the criminal underworld of Letheras, associated with a gang that coordinates for mutual protection. He is connected to the network of figures monitored by the mysterious operative known as the Waiting Man.<br>
Tehol Beddict	Middle of the three Beddict brothers, a Letherii citizen in his early thirties living in Letheras. Surprisingly fit and muscular despite minimal exercise, known for haphazard mismatched clothing assembled by his manservant Bugg. He is regarded as an idle, destitute figure about town, engaging in dry, cutting banter with Bugg that others find tiresome. Brother to Hull and Brys Beddict.<br>
The One Within	A mysterious entity referenced in the context of the Tiste Edur and the power that Hannan Mosag seeks to contact. The nature and identity of this being are left deliberately obscure.<br>
Theradas Buhn	Eldest son of the Buhn bloodline and brother to Midik, a Tiste Edur warrior of the Hiroth tribe renowned for leading seaborne raids during the Edur War of Unification. He bears a prominent facial scar — a seamed concave depression on the right side of his face from battle with the Merude — that has left his voice thick and blunted. He carries a broad-bladed cutlass and demonstrated loyalty to Rhulad Sengar. A capable and ruthless warrior with an unflinching demeanour.<br>
Tomad Sengar	Patriarch of House Sengar and father of the four Sengar brothers — Fear, Trull, Binadas, and Rhulad — with his mate Uruth. Once a rival to Hannan Mosag for the Tiste Edur throne, he later served as a Preda in the Edur military. He has dark eyes and large, scarred hands reflecting a life of conflict. Possessed of a strict sense of propriety, he judged his sons harshly for their conduct and was frequently and publicly dismissive of his youngest son Rhulad's immaturity, while showing pride in the accomplishments of his elder sons.<br>
Triban Gnol	Chancellor to King Ezgara Diskanar of the Kingdom of Lether, politically aligned with Queen Janall and Prince Quillas. Tall, thin, and elderly with dark eyes and long slim fingers he admires as artistic, prominent blue-green veins on his arms, and robes with heavy brocaded collars. Calculating and ambitious, he orchestrates significant political schemes to consolidate power and wealth, and nurses deep resentments against those who have crossed him.<br>
Turble	A money-lender operating in Letheras with no living family or relatives. He manages financial transactions and handles betting winnings for prominent figures in the city, including Finadd Gerun Eberict.<br>
Turudal Brizad	First Consort to Queen Janall Diskanar of the Kingdom of Lether. Handsome with soft, almost feminine features, remarked upon for his striking appearance. He leads an indolent lifestyle and maintains studied indifference in court. Ancient law denies him formal relationships or legitimate children. He mingles freely in palace life, and court rumours suggest intimate connections beyond his duty to the Queen. Brys Beddict finds him strangely disturbing.<br>
Ublala Pung	A half-blood Tarthenal from Letheras, towering in stature with enormous musculature, burnished skin marked by whip scars, a round face, pale eyes, and a thick neck. Possessing four lungs — a Tarthenal trait — he initially drifts through life unemployed before becoming a bodyguard. Regarded as innocent by nature, not particularly clever but defined by earnest loyalty and literal interpretations of instructions. Emotionally sensitive and gentle-natured despite his fearsome appearance.<br>
Udinaas	A Letherii male who serves as a slave in House Sengar of the Tiste Edur. Originally a young sailor indebted to a merchant, he was captured at sea and enslaved. He has regular, unimpressive features, a lean and tanned build, and typically wears coarse woollen trousers and a rope-belted tunic. Despite his harsh circumstances he maintains emotional connections with those around him and is capable of extending empathy to others, struggling with the moral weight of his choices. His bearing is noted by others as naturally kind.<br>
Ulshun Pral	Leader of the Bentract Imass in the Refugium. Short but powerfully muscular, with honey-coloured skin, overly long arms, thick shoulders, and numerous old injuries — a flattened nose, an inward-dimpled cheekbone, and a poorly healed forearm. He wears a roughly sewn cloak of mixed furs. A skilled cave painter who creates strikingly lifelike depictions of animals in motion, he demonstrates diplomatic ability when dealing with outsiders.<br>
Unn	An enormous young man with small eyes, of mixed Tarthenal-Nerek lineage, working on the harbour front in Letheras. He is the devoted guardian of six orphaned Nerek children and their grandmother Urusan, fiercely loyal and protective of his family.<br>
Unnutal Hebaz	Preda — Commander — of the Letherii army and considered its finest leader. Tall and fair-skinned with blonde hair and dark hazel eyes, in her forties with striking features whose beauty has only been refined by years of outdoor campaigning. A prudent, level-headed strategist, she is loyal to King Ezgara Diskanar and shows fond regard for those under her command, with quick tactical instincts and a disposition opposed to the Queen's political faction.<br>
Uruth	Full name Uruth Sengar; matriarch of House Sengar and wife to Tomad Sengar, mother to Fear, Trull, Binadas, and Rhulad. A Tiste Edur witch skilled in the magic of Kurald Emurlahn, she is a skilful weaver who maintains the family's bloodline tapestry, documenting the Sengars' history. A protective matriarch concerned with family honour and her sons' welfare, she is politically astute and willing to question authority when she perceives threats to her family's interests.<br>
Urul	Chief server at Huldo's establishment on Red Lane in Letheras. He wears a broad sash belt and is notorious among patrons for needing a bath, leading most to minimise their interactions with him. Anxious and easily frightened, he shows nervousness when encountering intimidating individuals.<br>
Virrick	A Letherii slave serving the Tiste Edur. Simple-minded with a fondness for secrets, he is fearful of authority figures and holds Rhulad Sengar in near-religious awe. He serves in a domestic capacity and acts as a messenger among the slave population, spreading information that helps maintain morale.<br>
Withal	A Meckros weaponsmith and master swordmaker from the Third Meckros city — a huge, bald, and muscular man with distinctive scarred wrists and forearms from his craft. He speaks the Letherii trader language. A war veteran who worked hard to avoid speaking of his experiences, he is reserved and rarely meets anyone's eyes when speaking. He holds a deep, philosophically grounded contempt for divine intervention, viewing Ascendants with deep contempt as dangerous and ungovernable forces, yet forms genuine loyalties with those around him. He is accompanied by three Nachts — Mape, Pule, and Rind.<br>
Yan Tovis	Also known as Twilight, the meaning of her name. Atri-Preda — a high-ranking military commander — in the Letherii army, stationed at Fent Reach and regarded as among the best commanders the Letherii forces have produced. Her eyes are the colour of weathered granite. Independent-minded and a capable strategist, she learns quickly and refuses to be controlled by external interests.<br>
